l, followed by Seyfert\ngalaxies. Our results indicate that the X-ray variability properties of 3C\n390.3 are broadly consistent with those of radio-quiet AGN, suggesting that the\nX-ray emission mechanism in 3C 390.3 is similar to that of nearby Seyfert\ngalaxies without any significant contribution from a jet component.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Aug 2009 17:43:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-08-06"}
